cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper deals with resource allocation and beamforming schemes in cellular networks, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes power allocation strategies, which fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of multiple antennas and beamforming also relates to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different approaches, which could involve machine learning or optimization techniques, falling under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
